
## Real Estate Price Prediction

### Goal

Develop and compare machine learning models to predict housing prices and identify the key features driving property valuation.

This project focuses on:

* Improving predictive accuracy across models
* Understanding which housing characteristics most influence price
* Demonstrating a reproducible ML workflow using Python

---

### Approach

Implemented a full modeling pipeline using both linear and tree-based methods:

* Applied log transformation to stabilize variance in sale prices
* Built scikit-learn pipelines for preprocessing and modeling
* Used feature scaling and imputation for missing data
* Estimated and compared multiple models:
    * Linear Regression
    * Ridge & Lasso (regularization)
    * Random Forest
    * XGBoost
* Evaluated performance using:
    * RMSE
    * MAE
    * R²

---

### Data

Data sourced from Kaggle’s
House Prices – Advanced Regression Techniques (Ames, Iowa)

* ~80 explanatory variables describing housing characteristics
* Includes structural, location, and quality-based features

    The Ames dataset is a modern alternative to the Boston Housing dataset and is widely used for applied machine learning practice.

---

### Results

* Tree-based models (XGBoost / Random Forest) outperformed linear models in predictive accuracy
* Feature selection (e.g., variance thresholding) improved model stability and generalization

Top Predictive Features:

* Overall quality of the home
* Above-ground living area (square footage)
* Garage capacity
* Basement quality
* Presence of central air conditioning

![Feature Importance](outputs/Picture3.png)

Key Insights:

* Structural quality and livable space dominate price prediction
* Some intuitive features (e.g., pool size) had minimal predictive value
* Model performance is sensitive to feature engineering and preprocessing choices

---

### Relevance

This analysis highlights how machine learning can be used to:

* Identify high-impact property features for valuation
* Inform real estate investment and renovation decisions
* Provide a framework for scaling to larger housing markets